  {% call components.section("Style") -%}

  <p>There are two link variants available for use.</p>

  <table style="width:100%;">
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <th>Variant Name</th>
        <th>Usage</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Inline</td>
        <td>The Inline link variant can be used inside of a line of text or paragraph to entice a user to take a less important&nbsp;action.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Call to action</td>
        <td>The Call to action link variant can be used on its own or near content to entice a user to take a more important&nbsp;action.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <br />

  <h4>Visual elements</h4>

  <p>Each link variant has different styles depending on how they are used with content.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Inline link</strong> - Text with or without a color or underline.</li>
      <li><strong>External link</strong> - Text with an external link icon to the right.</li>
      <li><strong>Primary or Secondary call to action link</strong> - Bolded text positioned inside of a background or border container.</li>
      <li><strong>Default call to action link</strong> - Bolded text that includes an arrow or icon to the right.</li>
    </ul>

