{% call components.section("Usage") -%}

  <p>Links should be used when a user needs to jump to content on the same page, visit a page within the same domain, or visit a page within another domain.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/link/when-to-use.svg' | url }}" alt="Link component usage" style="--inline-img-max-width: 754px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4> Content</h4>

  <p>Links are navigational elements, so the text needs to accurately communicate the destination. Inconsistent experiences might lead to distrust, lessening the satisfaction of a user during their journey. When writing link content, Inline links should be more descriptive to help a user better understand the destination whereas Call to action links should be more action-oriented to entice a user to make a selection.</p>

