  <h4>Images</h4>

  <p>Photos or images can be links as long as there is supporting content nearby explaining that a selection can be made, like a headline or Call to action link variant. Do not hide links in photos or images otherwise a user will miss the opportunity to make a selection if they cannot see the link.</p>

  <h4>Buttons</h4>

  <p>Do not use a link if an action should be triggered instead, like submitting a form, changing a state, or manipulating data.</p>

  <!-- Secondary text style -->
  <p style="color:#6a6e73; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; padding-bottom:16px;">Tip: In a Form, selecting a Button will perform an action whereas selecting the link will direct a user to a new page</style></p>

