  {% call components.section("Behavior") -%}

  <h4>Internal pages</h4>

  <p>If a user selects a link within redhat.com, they should be directed to content within the redhat.com domain. In this situation, a new tab or window is <b>not opened.</b></p>

  <h4>External pages</h4>

  <p>A user will be directed to another domain if they select the Inline link variant with an <b>external</b> link icon. For example, if a user needs to be directed to another website with different content or to complete a separate task, a new tab or window (depending on their browser configuration) is opened so they may complete that task and then return to the original task.</p>

  <!-- Secondary text --> <p style="color:#6a6e73; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; padding-bottom:16px;">Tip: Only the Inline link variant can include an external link icon</style></p>

